He Is Risen! From my family to yours, I am wishing a #HappyEaster to all who are celebrating today. https://t.co/0xEnOCXNB3

Western New York small businesses are vital to our region, so today I am calling on Congress to add additional funding to the Paycheck Protection Program. https://t.co/Tsw6ch3puu

In march Congress passed the DATA Act pushing for better broadband mapping. This a crucial first step for increasing internet coverage in rural communities. I plan to continue this effort in congress until all of #NY27 has coverage https://t.co/mVFW8B797B
I couldn’t agree with this more. We must never be dependent on China again for vital supplies for our nation! It’s time to put America First! https://t.co/NQHO8GCaWF

Thank you Jody Lomeo and local healthcare leaders for standing up and voicing opposition to the Governor’s abuse of power. We must stand united for Western New York and the health of our communities https://t.co/NNmsfMGvyu

Last Saturday, I held a virtual roundtable with farmers in Western NY to talk about how #COVID19 is impacting local agriculture. I'll continue to stay in contact with our famers and ensure we are doing everything we can to support them. https://t.co/QHdlRLPGuF
If you have medical or protection supplies and are willing to donate to help hospitals and healthcare professionals in New York State please email covid19supplies@esd.ny.gov or call 212.803.3100

.@realdonaldtrump & Congress are delivering big results for the people of WNY. Supporting our small businesses is vital to our region’s comeback & I urge small business owners to apply for the paycheck protection program at: https://t.co/ZtGrgIRZXs    https://t.co/Me4e4U2Vv1

Important info for voters in NY-27: The date for our special election has changed from April 28th to June 23rd due to the coronavirus. While the date has changed, the importance of winning this race has not. @realDonaldTrump and I are counting on your support on June 23rd. https://t.co/hqBBBcBYlM

This week I addressed the Wyoming County Chamber of Commerce virtually to share my plans to move our district forward, build our economy, and update our infrastructure. Watch my full address here: https://t.co/eOegBxntf3

By signing the CARES Act @realdonaldtrump gave the small business community a big win and reaffirmed his commitment to supporting America's small businesses. For more information visit: https://t.co/PGZooY7c6J

As someone who’s father was a Doctor who dedicated his career to helping his patients - this day holds special meaning. As our brave doctors fight to end the COVID-19 crisis, take a moment to reach out and thank them for their service on this day. We are all eternally grateful https://t.co/KiLHoaGKXt

Saturday I held a virtual town hall with farmers to discuss the impact of COVID-19 on agriculture in WNY. Our farmers are extremely important to keeping healthy food on our tables & I plan to do everything I can to help them prosper in Congress https://t.co/kNVo52U4S2

Thank you! https://t.co/ZVonisiSVo

When you’re looking for dinner options tonight, remember that many local restaurants and bars are offering takeout and delivery services, and they need your help. Order from your favorite pizza shop tonight and share on social media!
 https://t.co/pXys3KXJOS

@BellaviaMoh https://t.co/ewOENI45ef
Thank you! https://t.co/3o3KalgpDr

https://t.co/i27r4Rf0q0

It was great to speak at the second amendment town hall Thursday night in Niagara Falls. I enjoyed answering your questions and I promise to defend our #2A rights in Congress https://t.co/qsUPGxrFzd

Enjoyed great food and great people at the WyCo Chamber Pride of Agriculture Dinner. Congratulations to the Boxler Family for being awarded Agri-Business of the year! I look forward to working hard for our farmers and business owners in Congress #NY27 https://t.co/uvmnVIapc4
Great turnout today at the gun show in Cheektowaga, I look forward to continuing my defense of the second amendment in Congress #NY27 https://t.co/uCyiZZQVwS

Today I attended an Agriculture roundtable with Assm Hawley and Legislator Rath. It was an insightful meeting and I look forward to continuing this partnership with local farms in Congress to ensure we are doing everything we can to support the largest economic driver in #NY27 https://t.co/QJfGcaKR60

Great to join the Niagara County GOP last night for their annual Lincoln Day Dinner. Great crowd and congratulations to Senator Rob Ortt on being this year’s Honoree - a great Senator and leader for Western New York https://t.co/IVQG43CNhl

Last night I attended the Lake Ontario Preparedness Group meeting in Lewiston. It was a very informational meeting and I’m encouraged to see community members engaged and working together to solve this problem. I look forward to working with them in Congress #NY27 https://t.co/9HPqrsowUl

I strongly urge the IJC to examine every solution in their attempt to fix the disastrous flooding problem on our shoreline. I will be keenly focused on workable solutions to help provide much needed relief to residents & businesses along Lake Ontario https://t.co/0aRcWW3lIO
